"""
When to use function-based views:
- Simple logic
- Custom workflows
- Multiple forms
- Complex conditional rendering
- One-off functionality

When to use class-based views:
- CRUD operations (ListView, DetailView, CreateView, UpdateView, DeleteView)
- Reusable patterns
- Multiple views with shared logic
- Inheritance and mixins

Common generic views:
- ListView: Display list of objects
- DetailView: Display single object details
- CreateView: Create new object with form
- UpdateView: Update existing object with form
- DeleteView: Delete object with confirmation
- FormView: Handle form without model
- TemplateView: Render template with context
- RedirectView: Redirect to another URL

Common mixins:
- LoginRequiredMixin: Require login
- PermissionRequiredMixin: Check specific permission
- UserPassesTestMixin: Custom test for access
"""
